    <section id="import-auto-idm1198244240">
      <title>Addition</title>
      <para id="import-auto-idm1219194272">Adding two binary numbers is similar to summing two decimal numbers. For the positive numbers, the three methods (sign-and-magnitude, ones’ complement and two’s complement) are working the same. However, there is slightly different in adding negative numbers among the three methods.  shows the results of adding two 4-bit positive numbers. The results are obtained using a technique similar to the one that is applied to decimal additions. Note that there are carry digits shown on the table. Working from the right hand side to the left, if there are two 1’s to be added, write down the result 0 and put 1 as the carry for the next position; if there are three digits to be added, write down the result 1 and put 1 as the carry for the next position. </para>
