    <section id="import-auto-idm1038433120">
      <title>Hexadecimal to Decimal</title>
      <para id="import-auto-idm1040383792">Based on the definition, hexadecimal to decimal is straightforward. We only need to compute the sum of products. For example, converting <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block"><m:semantics><m:msub><m:mn>102</m:mn><m:mn>16</m:mn></m:msub><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">{102} rsub {16}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> to decimal as follows:</para>
      <para id="import-auto-idm1222714016">
        <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
          <m:semantics>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:mn>1</m:mn>
              <m:mi>×</m:mi>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:msup>
                  <m:mn>16</m:mn>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:msup>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>0</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:mi>×</m:mi>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:msup>
                  <m:mn>16</m:mn>
                  <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                </m:msup>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo>
                <m:mn>2</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:mi>×</m:mi>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:msup>
                  <m:mn>16</m:mn>
                  <m:mn>0</m:mn>
                </m:msup>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>256</m:mn>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>0</m:mn>
                  <m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
                <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                <m:mn>258</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:mrow>
            <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0">1× {16} ^ {2} +0× {16} ^ {1} +2× {16} ^ {0} =256+0+2=258</m:annotation>
          </m:semantics>
        </m:math>
      </para>
      <para id="import-auto-idm995437168">After server conversions, you will remember the powers of 16. It pays to remember these powers as they will help you convert numbers fast. Here are the first several powers of 16 worth remembering. </para>
      <para id="import-auto-idm948901584">
        <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
          <m:semantics>
            <m:mrow>
              <m:msup>
                <m:mn>16</m:mn>
